@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Installing Visual Studio 2022 for .NET Development";
}

<div class="container">
    <h1 class="text-center">Installing Visual Studio 2022 for .NET Development</h1>

    <div class="beginner-note">
        <div class="beginner-note-icon">
            <i class="fas fa-tools"></i>
        </div>
        <div class="beginner-note-content">
            <h4>Think of Visual Studio Like Your Digital Workshop</h4>
            <p><strong>Visual Studio = Your complete toolbox for building applications</strong></p>
            <p><strong>Simple analogy:</strong></p>
            <ul>
                <li><strong>Code Editor</strong> = Your writing desk and paper</li>
                <li><strong>Debugger</strong> = Magnifying glass to find bugs</li>
                <li><strong>Designer</strong> = Your visual layout tool</li>
                <li><strong>Build Tools</strong> = Your assembly line</li>
            </ul>
            <p><strong>In programming terms:</strong> Everything you need in one place to create amazing applications!</p>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="intro-section">
        <p>Welcome to your first step in becoming a .NET developer! Before we start coding, we need to set up our digital workshop. Visual Studio 2022 Community Edition is <strong>completely free</strong> and has everything you need to build web apps, desktop apps, and more.</p>
        
        <div class="alert alert-info">
            <i class="fas fa-info-circle"></i> <strong>Good to know:</strong> Visual Studio Community Edition is 100% free for students, open-source contributors, and individual developers. No hidden costs!
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Step 1: Download Visual Studio 2022</h2>
    
    <div class="installation-step">
        <div class="step-header">
            <div class="step-number">1</div>
            <h3>Visit the Official Website</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="browser-mockup">
                <div class="browser-bar">
                    <div class="browser-dots">
                        <span class="dot red"></span>
                        <span class="dot yellow"></span>
                        <span class="dot green"></span>
                    </div>
                    <div class="browser-url">https://visualstudio.microsoft.com/downloads/</div>
                </div>
                <div class="browser-content">
                    <div class="website-preview">
                        <div class="vs-logo">
                            <i class="fas fa-code" style="font-size: 40px; color: #5C2D91;"></i>
                            <span>Visual Studio</span>
                        </div>
                        <div class="download-buttons">
                            <div class="download-option">
                                <div class="option-header">
                                    <i class="fas fa-users"></i>
                                    <h4>Community 2022</h4>
                                </div>
                                <p><strong>FREE</strong> for students, open-source, and individual developers</p>
                                <button class="btn btn-primary">Download</button>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="step-instructions">
                <ul>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-mouse-pointer"></i> Click the <strong>Community 2022</strong> download button</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-download"></i> Save the installer file (about 2-3 MB)</li>
                    <li><i class="fas fa-play-circle"></i> Run the installer when download completes</li>
                </ul>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Step 2: Select What to Install</h2>
    
    <div class="installation-step">
        <div class="step-header">
            <div class="step-number">2</div>
            <h3>Choose Your Development Tools</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="workload-selection">
                <h4><i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i> Check these boxes (these are FREE):</h4>
                
                <div class="workload-grid">
                    <div class="workload-option selected">
                        <div class="workload-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-globe"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="workload-info">
                            <h5>ASP.NET and web development</h5>
                            <p><strong>Required for:</strong> Building websites and web applications</p>
                            <span class="workload-badge">Essential</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="workload-option selected">
                        <div class="workload-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-desktop"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="workload-info">
                            <h5>.NET desktop development</h5>
                            <p><strong>Required for:</strong> Windows desktop applications</p>
                            <span class="workload-badge">Recommended</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    
                    <div class="workload-option selected">
                        <div class="workload-icon">
                            <i class="fas fa-database"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="workload-info">
                            <h5>Data storage and processing</h5>
                            <p><strong>Required for:</strong> Working with databases</p>
                            <span class="workload-badge">Recommended</span>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="installation-size">
                    <div class="size-info">
                        <i class="fas fa-hdd"></i>
                        <div>
                            <strong>Total Installation Size:</strong> ~8-10 GB
                        </div>
                    </div>
                    <div class="size-note">
                        <i class="fas fa-clock"></i> Installation time: 15-30 minutes (depending on internet speed)
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Step 3: Installation Process</h2>
    
    <div class="installation-step">
        <div class="step-header">
            <div class="step-number">3</div>
            <h3>Watch the Magic Happen</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="progress-visualization">
                <div class="progress-step active">
                    <div class="progress-dot">1</div>
                    <div class="progress-label">Downloading</div>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-line"></div>
                <div class="progress-step">
                    <div class="progress-dot">2</div>
                    <div class="progress-label">Installing</div>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-line"></div>
                <div class="progress-step">
                    <div class="progress-dot">3</div>
                    <div class="progress-label">Configuring</div>
                </div>
                <div class="progress-line"></div>
                <div class="progress-step">
                    <div class="progress-dot">4</div>
                    <div class="progress-label">Ready!</div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="whats-happening">
                <h5><i class="fas fa-sync-alt fa-spin"></i> What's happening during installation:</h5>
                <ul>
                    <li><strong>Downloading components:</strong> Getting all the tools from Microsoft servers</li>
                    <li><strong>Installing .NET SDK:</strong> The core platform for running C# code</li>
                    <li><strong>Setting up Visual Studio:</strong> Installing the main program and features</li>
                    <li><strong>Final configuration:</strong> Making everything work together smoothly</li>
                </ul>
                
                <div class="tip-box">
                    <i class="fas fa-lightbulb"></i>
                    <div>
                        <strong>Pro Tip:</strong> You can use your computer for other tasks during installation. 
                        Just don't restart or shut down!
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <h2 class="text-center">Step 4: Verify Your Installation</h2>
    
    <div class="installation-step">
        <div class="step-header">
            <div class="step-number">4</div>
            <h3>Make Sure Everything Works</h3>
        </div>
        
        <div class="step-content">
            <div class="verification-steps">
                <div class="verification-step">
                    <div class="verification-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-rocket"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="verification-content">
                        <h5>Launch Visual Studio</h5>
                        <p>Open the Start Menu → Search for "Visual Studio 2022" → Click to open</p>
                        <div class="verification-image">
                            <div class="windows-search">
                                <i class="fab fa-windows"></i>
                                <span>Type here to search: Visual Studio 2022</span>
                            </div>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="verification-step">
                    <div class="verification-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-terminal"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="verification-content">
                        <h5>Check .NET Installation</h5>
                        <p>Open Command Prompt or PowerShell and type:</p>
                        <div class="code-snippet">
                            <code>dotnet --version</code>
                        </div>
                        <p>You should see something like: <code>9.0.100</code></p>
                    </div>
                </div>
                
                <div class="verification-step">
                    <div class="verification-icon">
                        <i class="fas fa-thumbs-up"></i>
                    </div>
                    <div class="verification-content">
                        <h5>Create Your First Project</h5>
                        <p>In Visual Studio, click "Create a new project" → Search for "Console App" → Click Next → Create!</p>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="success-message">
                <div class="success-icon">
                    <i class="fas fa-check-circle"></i>
                </div>
                <div class="success-content">
                    <h4>Congratulations!</h4>
                    <p>You've successfully installed Visual Studio 2022! You now have a professional-grade development environment ready to build amazing applications.</p>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="common-issues">
        <h3><i class="fas fa-exclamation-triangle"></i> Common Issues & Solutions</h3>
        
        <div class="issues-grid">
            <div class="issue">
                <div class="issue-header">
                    <span class="issue-badge">Issue 1</span>
                    <h5>Installation Fails or Freezes</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="issue-solution">
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Restart your computer and try again</li>
                        <li>Disable antivirus temporarily during installation</li>
                        <li>Ensure you have 15+ GB free disk space</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="issue">
                <div class="issue-header">
                    <span class="issue-badge">Issue 2</span>
                    <h5>Can't Find Visual Studio After Installation</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="issue-solution">
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Search in Start Menu: "Visual Studio Installer"</li>
                        <li>Click "Launch" from the installer</li>
                        <li>Check desktop shortcuts or Start Menu folder</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
            
            <div class="issue">
                <div class="issue-header">
                    <span class="issue-badge">Issue 3</span>
                    <h5>dotnet command not recognized</h5>
                </div>
                <div class="issue-solution">
                    <p><strong>Solution:</strong></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Restart Command Prompt/PowerShell</li>
                        <li>Restart your computer (refreshes PATH variables)</li>
                        <li>Reinstall .NET SDK from Visual Studio Installer</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </div>

    <div class="key-points">
        <h3>Key Points to Remember</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><strong>Visual Studio Community 2022 is completely FREE</strong> for learning and individual use</li>
            <li><strong>ASP.NET and web development</strong> workload is essential for this course</li>
            <li><strong>Installation takes 15-30 minutes</strong> – be patient!</li>
            <li><strong>Verify with <code>dotnet --version</code></strong> to ensure .NET is installed</li>
            <li><strong>Restart if you encounter issues</strong> – this solves most problems</li>
            <li><strong>You now have professional tools</strong> used by developers worldwide!</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="navigation-buttons">
        <a href="@Url.Action("Index", "Web")" class="btn btn-outline-primary ajax-link">← Chapter Introduction</a>
        <a href="@Url.Action("Introduction", "Web")" class="btn btn-primary ajax-link">Next: Introduction to .NET Programming →</a>
    </div>
</div>

